
The below command creates the ‘todo‘ topic with 6 partitions and with a replication factor of 3.

$  docker exec broker-1 \
    kafka-topics --bootstrap-server broker-1:9092 \
             --create \
             --topic todos --partitions 6 --replication-factor 3


To confirm the cluster setup we use the below command:

$  docker exec broker-1 \
    kafka-topics --bootstrap-server broker-1:9092 \
    --describe todos


connecting to cluster from client-

docker exec --interactive --tty broker-3 kafka-console-consumer --bootstrap-server broker-1:9091,broker-2:9093,broker-3:9094 --topic todos --from-beginning

localhost:9091,localhost:9093,localhost:9094

docker exec --interactive --tty kafka1 kafka-console-consumer -bootstrap-server localhost:9092,localhost:9093,localhost:9094 -topic producer_json -from-beginning